00:48:10.651 --> 00:48:17.039
30 years later, they're still holding it. You mention their name and they tremble; that's cancer.

00:48:17.040 --> 00:48:24.719
You don't want that in your life. I forgive them. My grandmother was like that.

00:48:24.720 --> 00:48:30.570
She had a very bad, abusive marriage the first time when she was young.

00:48:30.571 --> 00:48:39.862
My grandfather was very abusive and she carried that for the rest of her life and she died early.

00:48:39.863 --> 00:48:46.665
She got cancer and died. Bitterness is a cancer and you've got to let things go.

00:48:46.666 --> 00:48:53.690
My grandmother held that on there and every time you talked about them, she would get a snarl in her mouth. She'd just look at them like she wanted to spit.

00:48:53.691 --> 00:48:58.879
And I'm talking, they were divorced for years and she was married to another man and had kids by him and everything was fine.

00:48:58.880 --> 00:49:10.639
You would think so, but she took it into the next marriage. So I'm trying to tell you this: Don't take your drama from your last into the next.

00:49:10.640 --> 00:49:13.271
You may be here tonight and you're getting ready to get married.

00:49:13.272 --> 00:49:22.879
You've already been married before and you have bitterness towards your husband or wife and there's something eating at you still, but you're about to take it into your next marriage.

00:49:22.880 --> 00:49:28.462
You're about to take it into your next relationship. It cannot go with you.

00:49:28.463 --> 00:49:34.953
Leave the dirty laundry out. Leave the garbage out. Don't take it into the next one.

00:49:34.954 --> 00:49:38.909
Then people leave churches. They get offended. And then you go, 'Well, I'm leaving. I'm mad.

00:49:38.910 --> 00:49:44.135
I'm out of here.'And they take that offense and that bitterness into the next church.

00:49:44.136 --> 00:49:48.531
I've seen it time and time again when we worked at the church.

00:49:48.532 --> 00:49:53.921
We were there for years. And people—Sister Clipboard was all upset.

00:49:53.922 --> 00:50:06.479
She'd come in there with her list of clipboard issues and she would get mad and stay for five years or five months and she's out of there because she's upset and bitter.

00:50:06.480 --> 00:50:12.414
Did something happen? Okay. So, you've got to learn to let it go.

00:50:12.415 --> 00:50:22.829
Be like Elsa. Like, 'Let it go, let it go.'I was playing it on Christmas Day.

00:50:22.831 --> 00:50:37.838
'Let it go, let it go, let it go.'Hallelujah. You've got to let it go.

